1
00:00:29,190 --> 00:00:30,190
Alright Matsumoto-san.
Good luck!

2
00:00:30,260 --> 00:00:32,090
Yeah, I'm counting on you guys!

3
00:00:32,230 --> 00:00:35,970
"Matsumoto Hitoshi"
"Fourth year of Documental"

4
00:00:36,030 --> 00:00:37,570
—So this is your fourth year already.
—Yeah, that's right.

5
00:00:39,270 --> 00:00:43,640
The entire premise is that you can't smile.

6
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:45,540
And not being able to laugh

7
00:00:45,610 --> 00:00:47,780
is probably fun entertainment

8
00:00:47,840 --> 00:00:50,380
that I think anyone could watch.

9
00:00:50,550 --> 00:00:53,150
To put it simply, it's a battle
But if I had to compare it to something else,

10
00:00:55,650 --> 00:00:58,550
I'd say it's kind of like wrestling or martial arts.

11
00:00:58,620 --> 00:01:00,260
That's probably the best way to put it.

12
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:01,920
Yeah...

13
00:01:02,220 --> 00:01:03,390
You push like this...

14
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:10,270
Right now content has become very sensitive,

15
00:01:10,330 --> 00:01:14,240
and people are looking for seriousness.

16
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:16,140
And I think this show definitely

17
00:01:16,210 --> 00:01:18,240
goes against that altogether.

18
00:01:21,880 --> 00:01:23,980
—2000 pieces!
—2000?!

19
00:01:24,150 --> 00:01:26,180
Stop it! I'm feeling it!

20
00:01:26,550 --> 00:01:27,780
And if you think we're not being honest,

21
00:01:27,850 --> 00:01:30,790
you just have to make the offer to Sandwichman again.

22
00:01:30,850 --> 00:01:32,790
I don't think he'd ever return to the show.

23
00:01:34,990 --> 00:01:37,230
That's how it is.
It's just a fun idea.

24
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:40,640
If that were me, I wouldn't go on the show.

25
00:01:43,550 --> 00:01:49,840
But somehow, this show's... you know...
pretty vulgar.

26
00:01:50,170 --> 00:01:54,880
But at the same time, the winners are always unexpectedly

27
00:01:54,940 --> 00:01:57,180
kind of classy in their own way.

28
00:01:58,550 --> 00:02:02,620
I did it!

29
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:05,390
I think our ten members

30
00:02:05,450 --> 00:02:06,860
have a very documental-like

31
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:09,360
mental stability.

32
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:12,180
"The unflinching theoretical specialist"

33
00:02:12,550 --> 00:02:13,920
"The eternal extra"

34
00:02:14,190 --> 00:02:16,230
"Unbelievably supersonic"

35
00:02:16,920 --> 00:02:18,920
"The shrieking macho psychopath"

36
00:02:19,190 --> 00:02:21,130
"The full-fledged Afro-dite"

37
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:23,310
"The immovable backstage king"

38
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,010
"The uncrowned emperor of deceit"

39
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:28,010
"The very very very very late bloomer"

40
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:30,920
"The performer that kills performers"

41
00:02:31,190 --> 00:02:33,230
"The destructive bulldozer"

42
00:02:36,050 --> 00:02:37,850
"Hell's arbiter"

43
00:02:40,990 --> 00:02:42,530
Good work back there.

44
00:02:43,190 --> 00:02:45,230
Today I really feel

45
00:02:45,430 --> 00:02:47,460
kind of exhausted from laughing so much.

46
00:02:47,530 --> 00:02:51,130
I was almost crying. It was insane.

47
00:02:51,670 --> 00:02:53,940
I ended up feeling almost like

48
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:58,010
I wanted to see the world like they did.

49
00:02:58,310 --> 00:03:00,980
I kind of ended up admiring them somehow.
How should I put this?

50
00:03:03,110 --> 00:03:06,550
When they faced the challenge of laughing sincerely,

51
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:08,980
I feel that it turned out really well.

52
00:03:09,050 --> 00:03:10,850
It sure did.

53
00:03:10,990 --> 00:03:12,150
Well...

54
00:03:12,220 --> 00:03:13,220
It was amazing.

55
00:04:34,820 --> 00:04:40,120
This is a garden where dandelions blossom.
And white butterflies flutter around.

56
00:04:40,310 --> 00:04:42,910
The bugs enjoy their exercise in the summer, too.

57
00:04:44,410 --> 00:04:47,410
Alright then, allow me to give you some guidance.

58
00:04:48,010 --> 00:04:53,410
Would you gather a million yen for it?

59
00:04:53,910 --> 00:04:55,210
We're hosting a "Documental".

60
00:04:55,910 --> 00:05:00,310
The winner takes ten million yen.

61
00:05:01,210 --> 00:05:03,210
Of course, you're free to participate.

62
00:05:03,310 --> 00:05:08,910
Anyone strong enough to participate,
will be informed of the date, place and time.

63
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:11,910
I'm waiting for your reply.

64
00:05:13,510 --> 00:05:16,920
Here's hoping we'll get to spend many springs together.

65
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:21,820
Matsumoto Hitoshi

66
00:05:25,510 --> 00:05:29,910
"Enter the contestants"

67
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:38,270
Okay, that's the first one.

68
00:05:40,370 --> 00:05:41,570
Huh?!

69
00:05:44,540 --> 00:05:47,710
So this is how we're going to do it?

70
00:05:50,610 --> 00:05:52,750
I know about it. I've watched it.

71
00:05:55,380 --> 00:05:58,450
You can calm down somewhat when you do it for the second time.

72
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:00,860
It sure was fun, yeah.

73
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:01,920
I don't think

74
00:06:01,990 --> 00:06:03,430
that Junior is the kind of performer

75
00:06:03,790 --> 00:06:06,730
that naturally fits in "Documental" to be honest.

76
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:09,200
I think I can say it now that it's over,

77
00:06:09,730 --> 00:06:11,230
But I know my own weaknesses.

78
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:19,270
And I was thinking that maybe I shouldn't have called.

79
00:06:21,010 --> 00:06:22,410
I think it could be fun

80
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:25,680
to see Junior actually winning it or something, though.

81
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,680
(EN: Titles of each contestant are the same as the ones announced before)

82
00:06:29,420 --> 00:06:32,020
I wasn't expecting this.

83
00:06:32,090 --> 00:06:33,790
Alright...

84
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:36,760
There are many instances in this show

85
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:38,630
where people don't laugh as others keep trying.

86
00:06:38,690 --> 00:06:40,860
I wonder what kind of laughter

87
00:06:40,930 --> 00:06:43,130
Junior will be going for after knowing that.

88
00:06:46,870 --> 00:06:48,740
It's the same as the boxing ring.

89
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:51,510
Everyone participating is completely different.

90
00:06:51,570 --> 00:06:54,410
I'll use whatever I can,

91
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,780
and put up a good show.

92
00:06:56,850 --> 00:06:58,550
That's what I've been thinking.

93
00:06:59,550 --> 00:07:00,550
I see.

94
00:07:11,890 --> 00:07:13,760
Well, well, well.

95
00:07:13,830 --> 00:07:14,830
I see.

96
00:07:15,130 --> 00:07:16,730
Junior!

97
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:20,400
So that's how it is.

98
00:07:20,470 --> 00:07:22,100
Look who's here!

99
00:07:22,170 --> 00:07:24,270
—Kinoshita!
—Stop that!

100
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:28,010
Good work.

101
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,780
Alright, alright.

102
00:07:29,850 --> 00:07:31,650
Guess I don't have to read this.

103
00:07:35,850 --> 00:07:37,990
Make sure to watch this time again.

104
00:07:38,820 --> 00:07:40,860
"Don't you think you have a soft spot for Fujimon, Mastumoto?"

105
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:43,690
is something I've been told several times.

106
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:50,600
It's not that I have a soft spot for him in particular,

107
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:53,740
but I probably like him more than Yukkina. (EN: Fujimoto's ex-wife)

108
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:55,240
You see

109
00:07:56,340 --> 00:07:59,110
the timing is incredibly important.

110
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:00,980
I don't really know why, but...

111
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,480
but after seeing something funny,

112
00:08:02,540 --> 00:08:04,680
sometimes you don't feel much like laughing.

113
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,650
And I think that happens to me a lot in "Documental".

114
00:08:09,650 --> 00:08:10,920
Of course, Fujimon knows

115
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:12,590
that he has a particular power when he's in the background.

116
00:08:12,650 --> 00:08:14,320
And I don't think he intends to change that.

117
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:16,460
So he's set on winning somehow.

118
00:08:17,190 --> 00:08:18,830
Maybe he also needs the money.

119
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,500
Please make sure you watch again.

120
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:25,300
I don't think you've ever been teased this much

121
00:08:25,370 --> 00:08:26,570
by anyone else before.

122
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,300
I'm number one in the show business.

123
00:08:28,370 --> 00:08:31,040
So I'm going to grab it this time and counter attack!

124
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:38,650
Everyone will surely be thinking "ah, good to see Fujimon's doing well!"

125
00:08:38,710 --> 00:08:41,680
And that's just what I'm here to show.

126
00:08:44,650 --> 00:08:47,290
Hey, did you bring the 1.03 million?

127
00:08:47,590 --> 00:08:49,460
Why 1.03? It's just one million, right?

128
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:50,660
No, that's 30,000 short.

129
00:08:50,730 --> 00:08:52,730
When you called me to talk about your divorce,

130
00:08:52,790 --> 00:08:54,630
I had to call you back.

131
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:57,570
My long distance call ended up costing over 30,000 yen.

132
00:08:57,630 --> 00:09:00,670
That's not my problem. Not at all.

133
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:02,000
—Pay up.
—Let me tell you something.

134
00:09:02,070 --> 00:09:04,110
I was just in New Caledonia, and I didn't know.

135
00:09:04,170 --> 00:09:05,370
It's not my problem.

136
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,440
Pay them up already.

137
00:09:06,510 --> 00:09:08,540
What are you even talking about all of a sudden?

138
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:11,710
Hello there!

139
00:09:11,780 --> 00:09:13,920
Oh come on. He came in through that door?

140
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,080
That was unexpected.

141
00:09:15,150 --> 00:09:16,950
Yeah I guess.

142
00:09:17,020 --> 00:09:19,960
We're not supposed to be using that one yet.

143
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:23,790
I think it's fine to make an entrance like that, though.

144
00:09:26,730 --> 00:09:28,500
Hey.

145
00:09:33,770 --> 00:09:35,900
Sheeesh! (EN: Might be "How much!". Not 100% sure)

146
00:09:40,380 --> 00:09:41,540
Matsuo just...

147
00:09:41,610 --> 00:09:43,480
keeps getting funnier and funnier.

148
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:45,710
So I'm really looking forward to his performance.

149
00:09:45,780 --> 00:09:49,220
He might put up a good fight.

150
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,920
That's how I see it.

151
00:09:52,220 --> 00:09:53,560
I'm feeling pretty confident

152
00:09:53,820 --> 00:09:55,820
in participating in "Documental"

153
00:09:55,890 --> 00:09:56,890
as Ikko-san this time. (EN: Ikko is a Japanese make-up artist)

154
00:10:00,860 --> 00:10:03,100
Now people are laughing at his Ikko impression,

155
00:10:03,170 --> 00:10:04,600
but it just makes me sick.

156
00:10:04,670 --> 00:10:07,900
I just don't have a soft spot for it at all.

157
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:11,270
Even if I got the ten million,

158
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:14,080
I'd like to give at least seven million to Ikko-san.

159
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:17,880
Kind of like a deposit.
It'd be like a franchise.

160
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:21,850
No, you're not there yet.

161
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:24,120
Why?!

162
00:10:24,190 --> 00:10:25,420
Come on, drop it.

163
00:10:29,930 --> 00:10:33,430
I don't want it to be an impersonation making fun of her,

164
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:37,600
but rather a sign of respect.

165
00:10:39,170 --> 00:10:42,440
Okay, do it once in front of us.

166
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:43,570
Okay.

167
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:47,880
Sheesh!

168
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:50,350
It hasn't even started yet.

169
00:10:51,710 --> 00:10:52,880
You shouldn't do that anymore, though.

170
00:10:52,950 --> 00:10:54,020
Why?

171
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:55,680
It's gonna get old.

172
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:57,220
—Yeah, maybe...

173
00:10:57,690 --> 00:10:59,690
Wait... whoa!

174
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:01,490
Look, Junior-san.

175
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:02,560
Huh?

176
00:11:03,330 --> 00:11:04,330
Who's that?

177
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,300
Shoji?!

178
00:11:10,370 --> 00:11:11,800
—Good morning.
—Good morning.

179
00:11:11,870 --> 00:11:13,940
I'm counting on you.

180
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,040
I don't really know what you're going to do, though.

181
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:18,010
It's his first time.

182
00:11:18,070 --> 00:11:19,710
I can't imagine your strategy.

183
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,880
You said "Documental"?

184
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:25,950
I'm so happy!

185
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:28,880
Mikitty!!

186
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:34,190
I'm happy, but also scared.

187
00:11:34,290 --> 00:11:37,090
I entered this world because I admired Downtown so much.

188
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:39,030
The reason this is Shoji's first time

189
00:11:39,090 --> 00:11:41,630
is that I didn't think he'd be so good.

190
00:11:42,330 --> 00:11:46,400
To be honest, I thought that when he went all out,

191
00:11:46,470 --> 00:11:49,340
he was on about a fourth grader's level.

192
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:53,110
Mikitty!!

193
00:11:54,610 --> 00:11:56,580
He's on top of the world at the moment.

194
00:11:57,350 --> 00:12:00,650
And I think that happiness

195
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,620
may end up creating some kind of spark within him.

196
00:12:03,420 --> 00:12:04,420
—I'm counting on you.
—Shoji?

197
00:12:04,490 --> 00:12:08,290
The two successful lovebirds of the entertainment industry.

198
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,460
Which one of you is the loser?

199
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:11,960
I've been playing the role of dad

200
00:12:12,030 --> 00:12:13,930
a lot of the time recently.

201
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,130
But now,

202
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:19,470
I kind of want to show them my pride as a comedian.

203
00:12:21,270 --> 00:12:25,140
I don't want to crush them with technique, but with feelings.

204
00:12:25,210 --> 00:12:26,610
I have a one track mind.

205
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:28,480
I'll do my best,

206
00:12:28,540 --> 00:12:29,680
and pull off the unexpected,

207
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:31,450
with my soul.

208
00:12:31,510 --> 00:12:35,320
I think that I'd like to push forward with my soul.

209
00:12:37,650 --> 00:12:40,960
You'd have us all beat if we were cooking stew.

210
00:12:41,020 --> 00:12:42,660
That commercial was just—

211
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:43,730
Not yet!

212
00:12:45,430 --> 00:12:46,860
It's not the time to talk about that yet!

213
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,200
It doesn't matter, though does it?

214
00:12:49,260 --> 00:12:50,330
Leave it!

215
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,000
I'm telling you it's still too early!

216
00:12:52,070 --> 00:12:54,840
—What are you getting so worked up for?
—He's totally lost it!

217
00:12:54,900 --> 00:12:56,340
What are you so worked up for?

218
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:58,610
—He's too upset over nothing.
—I can't keep up with that.

219
00:12:58,810 --> 00:13:00,580
So the commercial...

220
00:13:00,980 --> 00:13:03,310
Stop it with the bullying already.

221
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:03,750
-Bullying?

222
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:05,250
-Someone's here. Look, look!
-Bullying?

223
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:05,680
-Someone's here. Look, look!

224
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:06,920
Who is it this time?

225
00:13:11,490 --> 00:13:12,750
Fujita?!

226
00:13:12,820 --> 00:13:14,990
Fujita!

227
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:18,090
This is looking bad!

228
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:20,600
You guys all look good!

229
00:13:22,430 --> 00:13:23,470
What's that?

230
00:13:23,530 --> 00:13:24,730
It's... it's that thing.

231
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:25,800
And here you were saying that you felt pretty confident

232
00:13:25,870 --> 00:13:27,400
I didn't say anything, and I'm not confident!

233
00:13:27,470 --> 00:13:28,770
I hope the other legends watch over him!

234
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:29,840
Too soon!

235
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:32,510
I really like Fujita.

236
00:13:32,570 --> 00:13:33,910
And I kind of think he's adorable.

237
00:13:37,310 --> 00:13:39,050
I've heard that Matsumoto-san really likes me.

238
00:13:39,110 --> 00:13:40,550
At least that's what people say.

239
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:44,550
Don't say that here.

240
00:13:44,620 --> 00:13:46,790
Also, I think that physically speaking,

241
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:48,490
Matsumoto-san likes me a lot better.

242
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:49,660
Get outta here!

243
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:52,890
This is his strength.

244
00:13:53,130 --> 00:13:54,460
He's funny,

245
00:13:54,530 --> 00:13:56,530
and he can do some pretty solid Manzai.

246
00:13:56,600 --> 00:14:00,170
So maybe he'll be able to pull off something good this time.

247
00:14:03,310 --> 00:14:07,480
He tends to play the tsukkomi much more than me,

248
00:14:07,540 --> 00:14:09,510
so he's not just going to sit around.

249
00:14:10,180 --> 00:14:11,850
He's going to go on the offense.

250
00:14:11,910 --> 00:14:15,450
I don't think they're expecting anything from me.

251
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:16,850
Nothing at all.

252
00:14:20,220 --> 00:14:23,330
I've been watching the series.

253
00:14:23,390 --> 00:14:28,800
And it's managed to make me laugh in a way nothing else had before.

254
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:30,330
So like...

255
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:33,240
Considering I hadn't really thought about being on it before,

256
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:36,970
I've decided to take a completely new approach.

257
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:40,710
Fujimoto-san, can you do this?

258
00:14:40,780 --> 00:14:41,940
I can!

259
00:14:45,580 --> 00:14:46,580
I don't like this.

260
00:14:46,650 --> 00:14:47,880
I'm telling you I can.

261
00:14:47,950 --> 00:14:49,480
I really don't want to do this.

262
00:14:49,550 --> 00:14:51,290
I don't want to go like this.

263
00:14:52,420 --> 00:14:53,620
Why don't we stretch or something?

264
00:15:02,730 --> 00:15:04,000
Really?!

265
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:05,930
Should've stayed backstage at Lumine.

266
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,200
This is Yoshimoto all the way.

267
00:15:07,270 --> 00:15:08,270
Cheers!

268
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:09,340
