Even if you try to put up a show on your own, you have to make sure you're not doing it for the wrong opponent.

291
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:18,710
That's why comebacks have to...

292
00:16:18,770 --> 00:16:22,000
hit them all at once.
Or you might end up bringing yourself down in the end.

293
00:16:22,010 --> 00:16:24,550
Besides, counter-attacks seem to
be able to make people laugh, too.

294
00:16:25,180 --> 00:16:27,680
I want to make them realize

295
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:30,150
that Koumoto's style is really unique.

296
00:16:30,220 --> 00:16:32,050
I want to make them learn something new.

297
00:16:35,690 --> 00:16:37,090
You heard them.

298
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:38,360
That doesn't matter.

299
00:16:38,430 --> 00:16:40,530
I can't listen to what someone tells me eight years later.

300
00:16:41,230 --> 00:16:42,500
I can see it already.

301
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:45,570
He does it in all his commercials and even on TV all the time.

302
00:16:45,630 --> 00:16:47,200
—I think he'll be out right away.
—He just loves it.

303
00:16:47,270 --> 00:16:48,640
—He loves those big smiles.
—I do.

304
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:50,840
—Speaking of which...
—Come on...

305
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:54,780
—The competition hasn't even started yet!
—The competition, yeah!

306
00:16:56,980 --> 00:16:57,980
Hey, nice going.

307
00:16:58,050 --> 00:17:00,820
For real?!

308
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:01,950
How many times are you gonna do this?!

309
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:03,890
Are you going to live here now?

310
00:17:04,090 --> 00:17:05,090
Excuse me.

311
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:06,960
No one said anything, though!

312
00:17:09,290 --> 00:17:11,090
It's here?
Okay, received!

313
00:17:11,510 --> 00:17:13,410
I've been short on money lately.

314
00:17:13,420 --> 00:17:16,230
And right now, business is going pretty bad,

315
00:17:20,770 --> 00:17:23,470
and well I have to pay rent.

316
00:17:24,370 --> 00:17:26,470
He's already well established.

317
00:17:26,540 --> 00:17:30,680
At least I think he is.

318
00:17:31,380 --> 00:17:33,380
This is something I heard at a certain massage place a while ago...

319
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:34,580
"You're..."

320
00:17:36,010 --> 00:17:39,510
"...Japanese. No way. You're. American!"
Or something like that.

321
00:17:40,610 --> 00:17:43,810
Those words gave me courage.

322
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,960
To be honest, I think Kobayashi is funnier

323
00:17:50,030 --> 00:17:51,600
when he's kind of...

324
00:17:51,730 --> 00:17:54,670
...surrounded by people more experienced than him.

325
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:58,140
It might be kind of difficult for him

326
00:17:58,210 --> 00:18:00,480
to be surrounded by mostly people younger than him.

327
00:18:01,410 --> 00:18:03,610
Every time I come here, I realize...

328
00:18:03,850 --> 00:18:06,050
...just how complicated laughter is.

329
00:18:08,150 --> 00:18:10,120
Everyone says

330
00:18:10,190 --> 00:18:11,290
that time flies when you're having fun.

331
00:18:11,350 --> 00:18:12,490
But frankly, I find it mostly exhausting.

332
00:18:14,620 --> 00:18:17,090
You don't even see six hour shifts in the adult industry.

333
00:18:19,730 --> 00:18:21,000
You're a regular now!

334
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:22,260
How many times has it been for you?

335
00:18:22,330 --> 00:18:23,330
This is Junior-san's second.

336
00:18:23,870 --> 00:18:26,100
—It's rough!
—I need the money.

337
00:18:29,570 --> 00:18:30,970
Nine years... once in nine years!

338
00:18:31,310 --> 00:18:32,310
Once in nine years!

339
00:18:32,370 --> 00:18:33,440
In nine years?

340
00:18:35,180 --> 00:18:36,950
No way!

341
00:18:37,010 --> 00:18:39,550
There he is!

342
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:41,480
I'm sorry!
Good morning.

343
00:18:42,050 --> 00:18:43,420
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

344
00:18:43,490 --> 00:18:45,020
Someone good just showed up!

345
00:18:49,290 --> 00:18:51,090
What's this?

346
00:18:52,390 --> 00:18:53,390
Me?!

347
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:55,600
I'm a crackpot underground comedian!

348
00:18:59,470 --> 00:19:01,070
This is from Matsumoto-san?

349
00:19:02,670 --> 00:19:03,910
He's from the same generation as Fujimon.

350
00:19:03,970 --> 00:19:08,580
He started performing at Yoshimoto 12 years ago.

351
00:19:08,780 --> 00:19:12,310
When I was in middle school, I became part of the Yoshimoto's NSC 8th generation.

352
00:19:12,450 --> 00:19:13,680
I got a little frustrated,

353
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:15,150
and my level kind of...

354
00:19:15,220 --> 00:19:18,090
...started to lag behind.

355
00:19:18,150 --> 00:19:19,650
8th generation!

356
00:19:19,820 --> 00:19:23,860
He was part of the 8th but eventually became part of the 13th.

357
00:19:24,430 --> 00:19:26,160
So we're coworkers too.

358
00:19:26,230 --> 00:19:27,400
We had a lot of peers.

359
00:19:27,460 --> 00:19:28,700
Yeah, lots of them.

360
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:35,300
I'm gonna do a coocoo clock now.

361
00:19:40,170 --> 00:19:42,080
I guess he's more primitive.

362
00:19:43,040 --> 00:19:45,510
I expect him to have a position

363
00:19:45,580 --> 00:19:49,350
kind of similar to Jimmy-chan.

364
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:51,990
Great Kinnikuman.
"Kinnikuman!"

365
00:19:52,390 --> 00:19:56,160
It may be a great chance for him.

366
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:59,330
If I end up going down,

367
00:19:59,390 --> 00:20:03,400
I'm not going to live the life of the underground comedian anymore.

368
00:20:03,460 --> 00:20:05,200
I'm carrying it all on my back.

369
00:20:09,340 --> 00:20:10,410
We met at 14, 15 years old.

370
00:20:10,810 --> 00:20:12,210
That's right.

371
00:20:12,970 --> 00:20:14,610
—And Oshiro is...?
—One year younger.

372
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:17,010
At the NSC...

373
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:19,210
He's younger than Junior-san?

374
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:21,180
—He was 14, I was 15.
—When was that?

375
00:20:21,450 --> 00:20:23,990
Second, third year of middle school.

376
00:20:25,390 --> 00:20:26,920
Look at that.

377
00:20:26,990 --> 00:20:28,220
I'm going to do a short skit.

378
00:20:28,290 --> 00:20:29,490
It's been a while.

379
00:20:29,790 --> 00:20:32,060
Skit: "Takeda-kun".

380
00:20:33,230 --> 00:20:38,070
Takeda! Snap!
Oh! I got Yoshida!

381
00:20:39,670 --> 00:20:40,770
O-hyo-hyo!

382
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:44,510
—This is...
—This is bad!

383
00:20:46,540 --> 00:20:49,340
That must've been like 30 years ago.

384
00:20:49,410 --> 00:20:51,580
30 years already?

385
00:20:51,650 --> 00:20:53,720
What were you thinking 30 years ago?

386
00:20:54,350 --> 00:20:56,180
The ninth one is here.

387
00:20:56,250 --> 00:20:57,750
He did the same thing twice.

388
00:20:58,590 --> 00:21:02,660
We could see you!

389
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:04,490
How many times has it been already?!

390
00:21:06,830 --> 00:21:08,360
Give it a rest!

391
00:21:08,430 --> 00:21:09,930
You've done it already!

392
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,800
It's been like six times already!

393
00:21:13,970 --> 00:21:16,200
Excuse me.

394
00:21:16,270 --> 00:21:19,910
I'm kind of used to it...
this red letter

395
00:21:20,170 --> 00:21:21,940
Alright, let's do this.

396
00:21:27,220 --> 00:21:28,720
I want to show them

397
00:21:28,780 --> 00:21:30,750
that I'm going to be relentless and the best.

398
00:21:31,210 --> 00:21:33,110
I'm kind of left wondering

399
00:21:33,110 --> 00:21:34,490
why does he still show up?

400
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:36,790
He's a semi-regular at this point!

401
00:21:38,590 --> 00:21:41,230
I'm thankful, though.

402
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:43,300
And my expectations have kept rising.

403
00:21:43,310 --> 00:21:47,560
Quitting while you're ahead is really lame.
So I'll keep coming back until they tell me to stop.

404
00:21:47,570 --> 00:21:49,240
I'd like to win it all, to be honest.

405
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,810
He's pretty good.

406
00:21:51,940 --> 00:21:53,140
He's insanely good.

407
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:54,710
We have a hell of a lineup.

408
00:21:54,780 --> 00:21:56,780
It's all Yoshimoto.

409
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:03,580
I don't want to see Kukky

410
00:22:04,450 --> 00:22:05,820
try his absolute best and go for the win.

411
00:22:05,890 --> 00:22:07,420
I want him to be out quickly,

412
00:22:07,490 --> 00:22:09,220
and see him as a zombie.

413
00:22:09,290 --> 00:22:10,430
If anything,

414
00:22:10,490 --> 00:22:11,490
his zombie performance

415
00:22:13,360 --> 00:22:14,560
might be pretty good.

416
00:22:14,630 --> 00:22:17,530
Every time I put in my all from the beginning.

417
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:20,070
I have almost no defensive barriers after all.

418
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:24,070
I think playing offensively is the best defense.

419
00:22:24,140 --> 00:22:26,970
It's just like boxing,

420
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:29,980
I want to at least create the opportunity to throw a jab.

421
00:22:30,280 --> 00:22:31,580
Because you won't hit anything

422
00:22:31,650 --> 00:22:33,080
if you don't throw the punch.

423
00:22:38,250 --> 00:22:40,050
I never expected this lineup.

424
00:22:40,120 --> 00:22:41,590
It's all Yoshimoto.

425
00:22:42,020 --> 00:22:44,930
—You're in Yoshimoto, right?
—That's right!

426
00:22:46,790 --> 00:22:48,560
The last one?

427
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,500
That's the last one, right?

428
00:22:54,140 --> 00:22:56,170
For real?!

429
00:22:58,140 --> 00:22:59,640
No, no, no, no!

430
00:22:59,710 --> 00:23:03,480
Even the brothers didn't know about it.

431
00:23:08,180 --> 00:23:11,120
It's here?
Thank you very much.

432
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:15,560
Ten million in front the family.
That's a lot of money.

433
00:23:15,620 --> 00:23:17,230
Of course, thanks to our dad,

434
00:23:17,430 --> 00:23:20,290
we saw a lot of scandalous things happen in private.

435
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:23,130
He looks happy to be on the show for the third time.

436
00:23:26,070 --> 00:23:27,140
Most TV channels

437
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:29,140
have already banned us altogether.

438
00:23:29,370 --> 00:23:31,170
And after a while,

439
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:33,340
we ended up on Amazon.

440
00:23:33,410 --> 00:23:35,440
So we're two regulars down, huh?

441
00:23:40,750 --> 00:23:43,150
Long time no see.

442
00:23:44,690 --> 00:23:45,890
With two brothers here...

443
00:23:48,390 --> 00:23:49,460
This is...

444
00:23:50,060 --> 00:23:51,130
You have memories and everything together.

445
00:23:51,190 --> 00:23:52,960
I may have some funny stories

446
00:23:53,030 --> 00:23:54,530
to tell about this guy right here.

447
00:23:54,730 --> 00:23:56,160
Just take each other out today, please.

448
00:23:56,230 --> 00:23:57,400
Yeah, destroy each other.

449
00:23:57,910 --> 00:24:00,010
How is it to record for six straight hours?

450
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:05,010
I've had to ride a bumpy bus in Africa for eight straight hours.

451
00:24:05,970 --> 00:24:07,740
This is nothing!

452
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:09,810
We have toilets and running water, right?

453
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:15,150
We have food, right?
Even stuff to drink...

454
00:24:34,740 --> 00:24:36,640
Seiji's here too?

455
00:24:37,040 --> 00:24:38,540
Seems like he's watching the TV.

456
00:24:38,610 --> 00:24:39,910
And Kukky too!

457
00:24:41,940 --> 00:24:43,740
How nonchalant!

458
00:24:44,050 --> 00:24:45,650
You sure look giddy today!

459
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:47,350
You jogging now?

460
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:50,250
I had enough with Sanma-san!

461
00:24:51,550 --> 00:24:52,550
He's Sanma-san!

462
00:24:52,620 --> 00:24:54,720
Okay everyone.
This is amazing!

463
00:24:54,790 --> 00:24:56,790
You're all getting along!

464
00:24:56,860 --> 00:24:57,860
This looks really fun!

465
00:24:57,930 --> 00:25:00,700
This might be the first time we've had an atmosphere like this!

466
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:01,930
Really?

467
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,460
Right? Don't you think so?

468
00:25:03,530 --> 00:25:05,530
Yeah, that's true.

469
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:07,070
We're testing each other.

470
00:25:07,130 --> 00:25:09,370
—This is great.
—They usually walk in smoothly and...

471
00:25:09,870 --> 00:25:11,370
It really feels like a dressing room.

472
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:12,970
That's right.

473
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:15,080
I guess it's because so many have been chased off the face of Earth.

474
00:25:15,140 --> 00:25:16,210
Stop it!

475
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:18,910
I'm sure it's just your imagination when talking about me, though.

476
00:25:18,980 --> 00:25:20,310
Imagination?

477
00:25:20,380 --> 00:25:21,750
I think it's looking pretty grim for you.

478
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:24,050
Yeah, but we can't screw up again.

479
00:25:24,450 --> 00:25:25,820
Sure.

480
00:25:27,390 --> 00:25:28,560
I'm sure Amazon doesn't mind though.

481
00:25:28,620 --> 00:25:30,420
Of course. Well... that's right.

482
00:25:30,490 --> 00:25:32,360
About Amazon.

483
00:25:32,430 --> 00:25:35,230
Uh... To be honest, I wasn't sure if I should say this.

484
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:37,370
This is Season 8, right?

485
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:42,970
And well, Season 7 got really good ratings,

486
00:25:43,370 --> 00:25:47,310
And Amazon was very pleased.

487
00:25:47,380 --> 00:25:49,840
They really want to keep "Documental" going,

488
00:25:49,910 --> 00:25:52,380
which is a huge compliment.

489
00:25:52,450 --> 00:25:55,750
So then we really got carried away and recorded.

490
00:25:55,820 --> 00:25:57,180
The next season?

491
00:25:57,250 --> 00:26:00,620
We recorded the next season...
And now it looks like it's not going to be released.

492
00:26:01,020 --> 00:26:02,020
Did something happen?

493
00:26:02,090 --> 00:26:03,090
What happened?

494
00:26:04,630 --> 00:26:07,260
Amazon's higher ups said

495
00:26:07,330 --> 00:26:09,500
that it was way too vulgar.

496
00:26:13,130 --> 00:26:16,000
That's fine! And I'm not trying to make a point or anything,

497
00:26:16,070 --> 00:26:19,410
just that even Amazon does have a line that we can't cross.

498
00:26:19,910 --> 00:26:21,810
-I see.
-A line?

499
00:26:22,180 --> 00:26:23,680
We don't know that line!

500
00:26:23,740 --> 00:26:25,050
So no vulgar jokes?

501
00:26:25,110 --> 00:26:26,410
No, no. You can joke around as much as you like.

502
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:29,450
It's really no problem at all.
It's just that you can't do absolutely anything.

503
00:26:29,520 --> 00:26:30,520
I see.

504
00:26:30,850 --> 00:26:33,290
But season 7 was pretty good.

505
00:26:33,750 --> 00:26:35,960
I see, so you guys went a bit too far.

506
00:26:36,120 --> 00:26:38,930
I mean, I'm even wearing an Amazon hoodie,

507
00:26:38,990 --> 00:26:41,930
to show how sorry I am.

508
00:26:42,330 --> 00:26:43,330
That's worse than I imagined!

509
00:26:44,670 --> 00:26:46,300
—So you're being polite?
—I am.

510
00:26:46,370 --> 00:26:47,470
I'm really being extremely polite.

511
00:26:47,540 --> 00:26:49,970
So that's why he walked in all jogging and everything?

512
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:52,140
All nonchalant!

513
00:26:52,610 --> 00:26:53,910
As an apology?

514
00:26:53,980 --> 00:26:56,680
Kind of.
Besides, a lot has been going on at Yoshimoto

515
00:26:56,740 --> 00:26:58,780
especially since last year.

516
00:26:58,850 --> 00:27:00,780
Ever since Chance joined Yoshimoto.

517
00:27:01,580 --> 00:27:02,580
He started this all!

518
00:27:02,650 --> 00:27:03,880
First I've heard of it.

519
00:27:04,690 --> 00:27:05,990
It might be true, though.

520
00:27:06,050 --> 00:27:07,250
For real.

521
00:27:07,320 --> 00:27:09,020
I'm counting on you all!

522
00:27:09,090 --> 00:27:12,160
And well, since everyone today is a Yoshimoto comedian.

523
00:27:12,230 --> 00:27:13,530
That's right.

524
00:27:13,590 --> 00:27:15,400
It's like a full-on Yoshimoto performance.

525
00:27:15,460 --> 00:27:19,170
Stop it! It all comes down to that?

526
00:27:20,530 --> 00:27:21,540
What?

527
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:25,570
You're all pretty self aware, huh?
Great intuition.

528
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:27,810
What does that T-shirt say if you read it vertically?

529
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:29,200
—What's written there?
—Why do you care? It doesn't make a difference?

530
00:27:29,240 --> 00:27:30,810
What's wrong with you, man?

531
00:27:31,910 --> 00:27:33,280
It's still too early for this!

532
00:27:33,810 --> 00:27:35,720
It's not early!

533
00:27:35,780 --> 00:27:38,550
If anything, doing this right now might be better.

534
00:27:38,620 --> 00:27:40,320
You're right.

535
00:27:40,720 --> 00:27:43,660
You sure love scandals, right?

536
00:27:44,130 --> 00:27:47,090
What's the deal with your big brother?

537
