556
00:28:30,570 --> 00:28:31,940
It's a hundred days, yeah.

557
00:28:33,970 --> 00:28:35,540
That's too real!

558
00:28:35,610 --> 00:28:38,350
From digging all those holes, huh?

559
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:43,320
By the way, here's my million.

560
00:28:43,380 --> 00:28:44,650
Thank you very much!

561
00:28:44,750 --> 00:28:47,860
So we need to add this, which gets us to 11 million yen.

562
00:28:47,920 --> 00:28:49,720
So this is my million.

563
00:28:49,790 --> 00:28:51,060
There we go.

564
00:28:51,560 --> 00:28:56,400
And we're gonna put this in here.

565
00:28:58,030 --> 00:29:00,870
No way!

566
00:29:00,940 --> 00:29:02,340
—That looks nice!
—Every time I see it...

567
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:03,500
It's just too much.

568
00:29:03,570 --> 00:29:06,470
I'm really giving this to you guys.

569
00:29:06,540 --> 00:29:09,180
Well, to the winner.
It's 10 million!

570
00:29:09,740 --> 00:29:12,080
No way! 10 million!

571
00:29:12,810 --> 00:29:13,810
I really want it!

572
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:15,180
It's really impressive.

573
00:29:15,250 --> 00:29:18,850
It is impressive.
Alright, that's that.

574
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:22,360
I ended up talking a bit too much.
Okay, six hours!

575
00:29:22,420 --> 00:29:25,360
Okay, so I've been thinking of getting more strict this time!

576
00:29:25,430 --> 00:29:27,260
At least that's the point.

577
00:29:27,330 --> 00:29:29,960
You can get a direct red now.

578
00:29:31,630 --> 00:29:34,030
If you get too careless.

579
00:29:34,270 --> 00:29:36,740
He's completely screwed.

580
00:29:36,800 --> 00:29:38,510
You've been laughing all this time.

581
00:29:38,740 --> 00:29:40,140
Junior too, yeah.

582
00:29:40,210 --> 00:29:42,280
That's just how I look, you know?

583
00:29:42,610 --> 00:29:44,250
—That's no good!
—Not at all!

584
00:29:44,310 --> 00:29:45,910
This is pretty bad news!

585
00:29:45,980 --> 00:29:47,080
Wasn't that a direct red?

586
00:29:47,150 --> 00:29:48,450
Well, I think Junior in particular,

587
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:52,290
you have to watch out and make sure your mouth is always slanting downwards.

588
00:29:52,350 --> 00:29:53,920
Junior's screwed, for real!

589
00:29:53,990 --> 00:29:55,160
You'd be out already.

590
00:29:55,220 --> 00:29:56,420
Alright, then...

591
00:29:56,490 --> 00:29:59,690
So no matter what happens, you can laugh or cry,

592
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:00,760
we're doing the whole six hours.

593
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:03,100
Let it end at four hours today, come on.

594
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:04,230
I think it's about time!

595
00:30:04,300 --> 00:30:08,070
Also, I told some staff to be on stand by around here, so...

596
00:30:08,140 --> 00:30:09,640
Make sure to use them if you need to.

597
00:30:09,700 --> 00:30:11,040
Sure, thank you.

598
00:30:11,710 --> 00:30:14,110
Good luck!

599
00:30:15,740 --> 00:30:20,350
Seiji's watch is a Louis Vuitton and that's hilarious for some reason.

600
00:30:20,410 --> 00:30:22,000
Well, I guess Seiji just likes that kind of brand.

601
00:30:22,020 --> 00:30:23,020
Luxury brands.

602
00:30:23,080 --> 00:30:26,420
Alright then. Let's start "Documental"!

603
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:32,160
There it goes!

604
00:30:32,530 --> 00:30:35,560
Oshiro has been pretty strict since 25 years ago already.

605
00:30:35,630 --> 00:30:37,200
That's just Oshiro.

606
00:30:37,530 --> 00:30:39,400
I'm sure people watching are now wondering

607
00:30:39,470 --> 00:30:42,200
just what is funny about Oshiro being that way.

608
00:30:42,270 --> 00:30:43,340
But for us laughing works

609
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:47,540
kind of like a Mobius strip.

610
00:30:51,350 --> 00:30:53,380
What's that right there?

611
00:30:55,250 --> 00:30:56,320
A hat.

612
00:30:56,980 --> 00:30:58,490
Yeah, a hat.

613
00:30:58,550 --> 00:31:01,320
I was wondering if there was something inside but didn't want to touch it.

614
00:31:01,490 --> 00:31:02,720
No, it's just a hat.

615
00:31:02,790 --> 00:31:05,290
It's a bontang made in Okayama.

616
00:31:05,360 --> 00:31:07,160
It's kind of stylish.

617
00:31:07,230 --> 00:31:09,300
—Huh? Where is this from?
—Okayama.

618
00:31:09,360 --> 00:31:11,830
—That's a school uniform?
—Yeah.

619
00:31:12,030 --> 00:31:15,240
I had it custom made to look like a uniform.

620
00:31:15,300 --> 00:31:18,210
It looks like a letter "M"!

621
00:31:18,270 --> 00:31:20,710
—For real.
—Are you trying to advertise here?

622
00:31:20,750 --> 00:31:22,710
For McDonald's?

623
00:31:24,380 --> 00:31:25,680
And these over here, too.

624
00:31:25,750 --> 00:31:26,980
Like the McDonald's logo.

625
00:31:27,650 --> 00:31:29,850
Are you going to start singing, too?

626
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:31,790
You should write "I'm lovin' it" right there.

627
00:31:31,850 --> 00:31:33,520
As a decoration?

628
00:31:34,220 --> 00:31:35,220
They're not coming?

629
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:39,390
Who?

630
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:43,300
You weren't listening. I told you already.

631
00:31:43,330 --> 00:31:45,300
Of course we're not going to run any McDonald's commercials.

632
00:31:45,370 --> 00:31:47,270
That's good.

633
00:31:47,500 --> 00:31:49,400
If we wrote "I'm lovin' it" right there,

634
00:31:49,470 --> 00:31:50,470
we could call it a commercial.

635
00:31:51,810 --> 00:31:53,940
I guess you're right.

636
00:31:54,110 --> 00:31:55,310
This is your first time, Shouji?

637
00:31:55,380 --> 00:31:57,710
It's also my first time, and I'm kind of happy to be here.

638
00:31:57,910 --> 00:32:00,810
You watched things like this, Seiji-san?

639
00:32:01,350 --> 00:32:02,680
—Sure.
—He doesn't look like it.

640
00:32:02,750 --> 00:32:03,750
At all.

641
00:32:04,150 --> 00:32:06,590
Huh? Really? I sure do.

642
00:32:06,650 --> 00:32:09,860
But I'm always drinking,

643
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:11,630
so I never get to know who wins.

644
00:32:11,690 --> 00:32:14,260
Call Mikitty to raise the curtain.

645
00:32:14,330 --> 00:32:15,500
You sure?

646
00:32:16,030 --> 00:32:17,400
—Let's make an announcement.
—And also,

647
00:32:17,460 --> 00:32:19,430
get Ikko-san to support you.

648
00:32:20,270 --> 00:32:21,670
Going through.

649
00:32:22,870 --> 00:32:24,100
Okay.

650
00:32:24,310 --> 00:32:25,340
Here we go.

651
00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:28,580
—Mikitty!
—Sheesh!

652
00:32:29,810 --> 00:32:32,080
—Mikitty!
—Sheesh!

653
00:32:33,210 --> 00:32:35,950
—Mikitty Mikitty!
—Shoulder throw!

654
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:40,190
—Mikitty!
—Sheesh!

655
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:44,020
—Mikitty!
—Sheesh!

656
00:32:46,930 --> 00:32:48,200
Junior!

657
00:32:48,330 --> 00:32:50,300
I told you!

658
00:32:51,530 --> 00:32:52,800
I told you about it!

659
00:32:52,870 --> 00:32:55,970
That was too fast!

660
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:57,300
Too early!

661
00:32:57,370 --> 00:32:58,470
He's the worst among us!

662
00:32:58,540 --> 00:33:00,040
No way!

663
00:33:00,110 --> 00:33:02,140
That's too fast!

664
00:33:02,410 --> 00:33:05,910
Okay, Junior.
You were smiling normally.

665
00:33:05,980 --> 00:33:08,050
Isn't that the fastest in "Documental" history?

666
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:09,380
I think it's probably the fastest.

667
00:33:09,450 --> 00:33:10,750
That's no good.

668
00:33:10,820 --> 00:33:12,650
We couldn't let that slip by.

669
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:14,250
What just happened, really?

670
00:33:14,320 --> 00:33:16,160
How disappointing!

671
00:33:16,920 --> 00:33:19,630
—Mikitty Mikitty!
—Shoulder throw!

672
00:33:21,200 --> 00:33:24,200
—Mikitty!
—Sheesh!

673
00:33:25,100 --> 00:33:27,530
—Mikitty!
—Sheesh!

674
00:33:29,540 --> 00:33:30,540
He was way out of line!

675
00:33:31,740 --> 00:33:33,070
What a spoiled brat!

676
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:35,480
To be honest, I was waiting for it.

677
00:33:35,540 --> 00:33:36,840
But you're supposed to be more strict this time.

678
00:33:36,910 --> 00:33:38,580
That's a straight red.

679
00:33:38,650 --> 00:33:42,620
